of the year ♪

13:31.459 --> 13:33.960
♪ <i>January</i> ♪

13:33.962 --> 13:37.630
♪ You start the year all fine... ♪
Well, well, well.

13:38.700 --> 13:40.099
- Hi.
- Hey.

13:40.101 --> 13:43.469
You say you're busy as bees,
yet here you are, dancing.

13:43.471 --> 13:45.772
Although I suppose
bees do dance,

13:45.774 --> 13:48.207
but their dance lets other bees
know where the pollen is,

13:48.209 --> 13:49.509
and yours does not.

13:49.511 --> 13:53.980
So my logic, despite
that slight detour, does track.

13:54.883 --> 13:57.417
We're just waiting
for my code to compile.

13:57.419 --> 13:58.985
What are you doing here?
I stopped by

13:58.987 --> 14:01.220
to see if you wanted
to go to the movies with me.

14:01.222 --> 14:02.822
Well, I-I'd love to,

14:02.824 --> 14:05.358
but we're just about
to test the interface.

14:05.360 --> 14:06.426
It could take a while.

14:06.428 --> 14:08.695
Okay, buddy, it--
it's not my place,

14:08.697 --> 14:11.898
but Bernadette's been
feeling a little abandoned

14:11.900 --> 14:13.866
with all the hours that
you've been putting in.

14:13.868 --> 14:16.169
You just asked him
to go to the movies.

14:16.171 --> 14:17.770
Yeah, but our weird
relationship was grandfathered

14:17.772 --> 14:21.107
into their marriage,
and yours was not.

14:23.178 --> 14:26.979
Okay, I put new batteries
in the smoke detectors.

14:26.981 --> 14:28.514
Did you do the laundry?

14:28.516 --> 14:29.982
I sure did. Ooh.

14:29.984 --> 14:32.485
He's gonna be steamed.

14:32.487 --> 14:34.754
Just like his dress shirts.

14:35.690 --> 14:37.590
At least he can still
clean the oven,

14:37.592 --> 14:38.825
so that's something.

14:38.827 --> 14:40.626
Oh, that's what he thinks.
Where's your steel wool?

14:40.628 --> 14:42.729
Right here.

14:42.731 --> 14:45.031
We make quite the team.

14:45.033 --> 14:47.200
Sure do.

14:48.069 --> 14:49.969
Guys, you won't believe this.

14:49.971 --> 14:52.939
I stopped by the university
to check in on Howard and Amy,

14:52.941 --> 14:54.373
and they were having fun.

14:54.375 --> 14:56.142
Well, don't worry.
He won't be having any fun

14:56.144 --> 14:57.310
when he gets home.

14:57.312 --> 14:59.112
I did all his favorite chores.

15:00.181 --> 15:01.514
What are you talking about?

15:01.516 --> 15:03.483
Howard hates doing chores.

15:03.485 --> 15:05.651
Wait, then why would Bernadette
tell me that... (gasps)

15:05.653 --> 15:07.854
Bernadette.

15:09.758 --> 15:11.791
Did you play on my well
established gullibility

15:11.793 --> 15:13.226
to clean your house?

15:13.228 --> 15:15.862
Sure did.

15:15.864 --> 15:18.564
Well, I would storm out of here,

15:18.566 --> 15:20.733
but I already have
the gloves and the steel wool,

15:20.735 --> 15:24.070
and I really do love
cleaning an oven. Move.

15:25.240 --> 15:27.140
She made me do all her chores,

15:27.142 --> 15:29.008
and it wasn't even her
idea-- she stole it

15:29.010 --> 15:31.577
from <i>Tom Sawyer.</i>

15:31.579 --> 15:33.212
You know what? This is crazy.

15:33.214 --> 15:35.882
Howard and Amy are working
together-- get over it.

15:35.884 --> 15:36.916
Leonard, what are you doing?

15:36.918 --> 15:38.084
“Knowing when to say when.”

15:38.086 --> 15:39.418
This is not a big deal.

15:39.420 --> 15:40.853
It <i>is</i> a big deal.

15:40.855 --> 15:43.823
Howard's getting Amy used to
laughing and listening to music.

15:43.825 --> 15:46.592
What if she expects
that madness at home?

15:46.594 --> 15:48.327
Yeah, that is a good point.
I'm really proud of the way

15:48.329 --> 15:49.796
you're able to express
your feelings.

15:49.798 --> 15:50.930
SHELDON:
Thank you.

15:50.932 --> 15:52.131
I'm just so angry.

15:52.133 --> 15:53.199
You know,

15:53.201 --> 15:54.534
everyone gets angry.

15:54.536 --> 15:58.237
Even mommies and daddies.

15:59.641 --> 16:01.174
You can't think
this is the right time

16:01.176 --> 16:02.875
to “validate his behavior.”

16:02.877 --> 16:05.278
Okay, what about
“presenting a united front”?

16:05.280 --> 16:07.246
What about you coddling him
and he's never gonna learn?

16:07.248 --> 16:08.548
Look.

16:08.550 --> 16:12.151
You sound frustrated,
and I'm really proud of the way

16:12.153 --> 16:15.221
you're able to state
your opinion.

16:15.223 --> 16:16.956
Thank you.

16:16.958 --> 16:18.624
Wait, no, no.

16:19.627 --> 16:21.394
Don't use that book on me.

16:21.396 --> 16:22.495
SHELDON:
W-Wait,

16:22.497 --> 16:23.496
what book?

16:23.498 --> 16:24.664
(groans) Penny's been using

16:24.666 --> 16:26.666
one of Bernadette's
parenting books on you.

16:26.668 --> 16:28.367
What? So has he.

16:28.369 --> 16:31.537
Wh-What makes you think
you can treat me like a child?

16:34.576 --> 16:38.611
Your shampoo comes
in a Big Bird bottle.

16:38.613 --> 16:41.147
That's because the adult shampoo
burns my man eyes.

16:45.186 --> 16:47.320
Hey, what are you working on?

16:47.322 --> 16:49.655
Oh, my God, you're still here?

16:51.860 --> 16:52.925
Well, of course I'm here.

16:52.927 --> 16:55.127
I know what
you're going through.

16:55.129 --> 16:58.965
Really? You have a needy
Indian man in your house?

16:59.968 --> 17:02.235
I did,
but then he came over here.

17:04.105 --> 17:06.137
So is this how it's gonna be
if we have kids?

17:06.140 --> 17:07.772
You're just gonna
throw me under the bus?

17:07.775 --> 17:10.041
If you spoil them the way you do
Sheldon, then, yeah.

17:10.044 --> 17:11.344
Uh, my way was working.

17:11.346 --> 17:12.578
Okay? I think you're just upset

17:12.579 --> 17:14.914
because there are some things
I am better than you at.

17:14.915 --> 17:16.616
Well, you can't end a sentence
with a preposition,

17:16.617 --> 17:18.084
so clearly, not grammar.

17:19.354 --> 17:21.621
If you're so smart,
was that a smart thing to say?

17:21.623 --> 17:22.755
That depends. Before I said it,

17:22.757 --> 17:24.223
was sex tonight
still on the table?

17:24.224 --> 17:25.925
No.
Then it's fine.

17:28.096 --> 17:30.563
You know, once we get this
operational,

17:30.565 --> 17:33.165
we could probably figure out
how to make it wireless.

17:33.167 --> 17:35.167
That'd be amazing.

17:35.169 --> 17:36.369
(phone chimes)

17:36.371 --> 17:38.671
Oh, that's Sheldon.

17:38.673 --> 17:40.773
Oh, he's upset with
Leonard and Penny.

17:40.775 --> 17:42.308
(phone whooshes)

17:42.310 --> 17:43.676
And Bernadette.

17:43.678 --> 17:45.144
(phone whooshes)

17:45.146 --> 17:46.512
And Mark Twain.

17:49.684 --> 17:51.517
Yeah, Bernadette
texted earlier.

17:51.519 --> 17:53.819
Raj is really getting
on her nerves.

17:53.821 --> 17:55.855
Well, I guess we have
been working late a lot.

17:55.857 --> 17:56.956
(sighs)

17:56.958 --> 17:58.791
Should we call it a
night and go home?

17:58.793 --> 18:01.894
Or we could brew a pot
of coffee and power through.

18:01.896 --> 18:04.563
I don't know,
it's getting kind of late.

18:04.565 --> 18:06.732
Hey, where's my watch?

18:06.734 --> 18:07.867
Why don't you ask

18:07.869 --> 18:09.502
your skeleton?

18:11.906 --> 18:13.839
(Amy gasps)

18:13.841 --> 18:15.675
Oh, my God.

18:15.677 --> 18:18.044
How is that even possible?!

18:26.483 --> 18:28.992
This is great,
the two of us hanging out.

18:28.994 --> 18:30.327
Why didn't we think
of this earlier?

18:30.329 --> 18:31.428
Agreed.

18:31.430 --> 18:33.230
I don't need Amy
to watch a movie.

18:33.232 --> 18:36.032
I can not hold your
hand just as easily.

18:36.034 --> 18:38.235
(music begins playing over TV)

18:40.772 --> 18:45.475
In the book this is based
on, that man's the killer.

